A female student of the Delta State Polytechnic, Ozoro, Isoko North Locak Government Area, has been hacked to death by her lover over allegations of infidelity, The Nation has learnt. It was equally said that the lovers cohabited off campus in a rented room. The suspect is a graduate of the institution. Sources said trouble started after the suspect accused the deceased of infidelity on Saturday night and a fight broke out leading to her death. They both have a child together. The suspect took the body of the lady to the State General Hospital in the morning where she was confirmed dead, it was learnt. A source, speaking on condition of anonymity, said, “ It happened today (Saturday) at Ozoro. A guy beat his girlfriend to death with a machete.   Gunmen abduct expectant mum, 11 others in Kaduna, Anambra      Abducted NDDC official freed in Imo     ‘Seven died, 100 injured in road crashes during Sallah in…   “People said he did it under the influence, and that he didn’t run away after killing her. Instead, he rushed her to a general hospital. “I just confirmed that the girl was a student of the school, but the guy is not. Maybe he has graduated. “The guy must have been on drugs last night It was this morning that the guy regained himself. “After seeing what he had done, he rushed the girl to the hospital.” A video footage seen by this reporter showed a female body lying on a stretcher while the suspect was being flogged with a cane by a mob. Efforts to reach police spokesman DSP Bright Edafe, proved abortive as he neither took his call nor responded to the correspondent’s text message.